Bayelsa State Government has announced an increase in the cash rewards for its female club side, the Bayelsa Queen’s, ahead of the Nigeria Women’s Football League Super 6 Championship. The government said yesterday it had increased the N1m cash gift for every match won to N1.5m, while goal-scorers would get N200, 000 for each goal as against the previous N150, 000. The state Deputy Governor, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, made the announcement while addressing the management and players of the team at the Samson Siasia Sports Complex, Yenagoa at the end of the weekly Prosperity Walk. This is coming ahead of preparations for the Nigerian Women’s Football League Super 6 championship, scheduled to begin on May 16 to 22 in Benin, Edo State capital.   Mike Ezuruonye seals endorsement deal with Checkers Custard     Intrigues stall special agro–industrial processing zones…     Buhari appeals to ASUU, students   A statement by the Senior Special Assistant on Media to the Deputy Governor, Doubara Atasi, explained that the first assist for every goal scored would get a N150, 000, while N100, 000 each was earmarked for second and third assists. According to the statement, the Office of the Deputy Governor also made a donation of N2m to the Queens for topping the just concluded Female Professional League table. Also lending the support to the team, the Wife of the State Governor, Dr. Gloria Diri, thanked the team for always bringing laurels to the state and charged them to repeat the feat once more as they do battle at the Super Six Championship in Edo State. Meanwhile, Governor Douye Diri has hailed Sports Commissioner, Dr. Daniel Igali, over his recent award as Sports Man of the Year by Sun Newspapers.